<div>
  <h2>Why is target='_blank' vulnerable?</h2>
  
  <p><em>target=_blank</em> allows the new opened tab direct access to the origin's tab through the <code>opener</code> object.</p>
  <p>For example, try clicking on <a href="https://httpsecurityheaders.applephi.net/Vulnerable/SameOrigin" target="_blank">this vulnerable link</a></p>
  
  <p><code>
  &lt;a href="https://httpsecurityheaders.applephi.net/Vulnerable/SameOrigin" target="_blank"&gt;Link&lt;/a&gt;
  </code></p>
  
  <p>In this innocent example I modify the web page a little, but you could replace the page with a phishing page...</p>
</div>

<div>
<h2>How can I fix this?</h2>
  <p>You can easily fix this by setting the <code>rel</code> attribute to <code>noopener</code>. This way the new tab does not receive the opener object.</p>
  <p>For example, try clicking on <a href="https://httpsecurityheaders.applephi.net/Vulnerable/SameOrigin" target="_blank" rel="noopener">this safe link</a></p>
  
  <p><code>
  &lt;a href="https://httpsecurityheaders.applephi.net/Vulnerable/SameOrigin" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Link&lt;/a&gt;
  </code></p>
</div>

